        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>IMPERIAL CHEMICAL CO.&#44;<lb/>
                FOR THE MANUFACTURE OF<lb/>
                Boiler Compounds.<lb/></p>
            <p>ALFRED MYERS&#44;<lb/> GENERAL MANAGER<lb/>
                OUR GUARANTEES.<lb/> CONTAIN NO ACID OR INGREDIENTS TO INJURE<lb/> BRASS&#44; IRON OR PACKING.<lb/> SATISFACTORY RESULT CONDITION OF PAYMENT.<lb/></p>
            <p>OFFICE AT SOHO MACHINE WORKS&#44;<lb/> ESPLANADE<lb/>
                Toronto&#44; Novr 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1890<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Esteemed Friend&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>A letter from me may<lb/> seem strange and so it is&#44;<lb/> but as much as we neglect<lb/> our friends&#44; when we want to<lb/> make use of them can always<lb/> find the time to address them&#44;<lb/> however I trust the purport<lb/> of this will be sufficient<lb/> <sic>apoligy</sic> for intruding on<lb/> your valuable time&#44; just<lb/> let me enquire after the<lb/> health of all your circle<lb/> including of course our dear<lb/> grand children &#38; hope all is<lb/> going as nicely.<lb/></p>
            <p>Now to the subject I would<lb/> bring to your notice&#44;<lb/> we have in this country a<lb/> day set apart as in the<lb/> United States as a day of &#34;Thanksgiving&#34;<lb/> <sic>orderd</sic> by the <sic>Governer</sic> General<lb/> the same as by the Presidents&#44;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>this day has never been observed<lb/> by the Jews of this place &#38; are<lb/> about the only faith whose<lb/> place of worship is not open&#39;d.<lb/>  I have introduced a resolution that<lb/> hereafter it shall be observed<lb/> by the Jews of Toronto.  Now I<lb/> fancy there is &#38; will be much<lb/> opposition to this from the fact<lb/> we have here a large element<lb/> of ignorant &#38; <sic>predjudiced</sic>&#61; Jews<lb/> who think we are <sic>apeing</sic> the<lb/> gentile ideas by taking the steps<lb/> proposed&#44; they do not enter into<lb/> the spirit of being &#34;<hi rend="underline">Citizens</hi>&#34;<lb/> they only think they are &#34;<hi rend="underline">Jews</hi>&#34;<lb/> now what I would esteem<lb/> a favor from you would be<lb/> a letter giving your views<lb/> from of course the strict<lb/> orthodox stand&#45;point &#38; so I<lb/> can show them the argument<lb/> of one whom all consider the<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>upholder of orthodoxy in America.<lb/>  I think you will understand<lb/> the favor I ask&#44; we have a<lb/> hard set here I assure you&#44;<lb/> only a very few who can be<lb/> called respectable &#38; aim at<lb/> being respected&#44; there is very<lb/> much feeling against the<lb/> Jews here &#38; the general public<lb/> lose no opportunity of casting<lb/> the slur.  It is to try &#38; remove<lb/> these ideas that a few of us<lb/> are making the effort to<lb/> raise the name to the standard<lb/> it should hold but am<lb/> afraid it will be hard task.<lb/>  Thanking you in advance for<lb/> your esteemed reply &#38; with<lb/> kind regards to all united<lb/> by my wife &#38; Fannie<lb/> yours very sincerely<lb/> Alfred Myers<lb/></p>
            </body>
